# Node runtime (Cursor only)

Cursor agent shells often default to an old nvm Node (e.g. v18). That breaks Vitest, Biome, and `undici` here. Other harnesses usually already run Node 25 — they do not need extra nvm steps.

Before `npm run check`, `npm test`, or other Node commands in this repo:

```bash
nvm use    # reads .nvmrc (25); run `nvm install` once if missing
node -v    # should print v25.x
```

`npm run check` and `npm test` also run `check:node`, which fails fast on Node < 25.
